  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should every first time anime convention goer know?",
  "response": "Attending an anime convention for the first time can be an exciting and overwhelming experience. Here are some essential tips to help you make the most of your time:\n\n1. **Plan Ahead**: Familiarize yourself with the schedule of events, panels, screenings, and workshops. Highlight your must-see events to avoid conflicts.\n\n2. **Purchase Tickets Early**: If possible, buy your tickets in advance to avoid long lines at the venue. Many conventions offer discounts for early registration.\n\n3. **Cosplay Considerations**: If you plan to cosplay, choose a costume that is comfortable and manageable for long hours. Be prepared for photos and interactions as many attendees will want to take pictures with you.\n\n4. **Stay Hydrated and Eat Well**: Conventions can be exhausting, so keep hydrated and eat healthy snacks to maintain your energy throughout the day.\n\n5. **Know the Venue**: Get familiar with the layout of the venue. Find out where essential places are located, such as panels, restrooms, and food concessions.\n\n6. **Be Respectful**: Remember that conventions are about community and shared interests. Be respectful to other attendees and their personal space, especially in crowded areas or when taking photos.\n\n7. **Budget Your Money**: Bring cash for vendors, as not all may accept credit or debit cards. Set a budget for merchandise, food, and any other expenses.\n\n8. **Bring Essentials**: Pack a small bag with essentials like a water bottle, portable charger, snacks, schedule, and any personal items you might need.\n\n9. **Participate in Activities**: Engage in games, workshops, and discussions. It\u2019s a great way to meet people and share your love for anime and manga.\n\n10. **Network**: Meet fellow fans, make new friends, and exchange social media handles. The community is one of the best aspects of conventions.\n\n11. **Respect Cosplay Etiquette**: Always ask permission before taking photos of someone in costume, and avoid touching their costumes without consent.\n\n12. **Stay Safe**: Be aware of your surroundings, and know where the nearest exits are located. If you feel uncomfortable or unsafe, don\u2019t hesitate to seek help from security.\n\n13. **Have Fun**: Lastly, relax and enjoy the experience! Conventions are all about celebrating your passions, so take time to enjoy panels, exhibits, and hang out with friends.\n\nFollowing these tips will help ensure that your first anime convention experience is memorable and enjoyable.",
